# Results

In the result section, I can talk about my data.
For example, I can report the mean differences in SCRs between females and males, `r print_mean_sd(dataSCR$raw.ampl, na.rm=TRUE)`.
I can also report the results of a t-test where I tested for differences in SCRs between *females* and *males*, `r print_ttest(ttest_sex_diff)`, $d =$ `r round(cohensD_ttest_sex_diff$Cohens_d, 2)`.

Furthermore, you can include a cross reference to Figure \@ref(fig:results-include-figure1).


